nch to shared glycine target step\",\n      \"description\": \"Surface glyoxylate and malonate chemistry with ammonia generates oxaloacetate-class intermediates in parallel with glycine production from the same C1/HCN feedstock network; both branches converge on the final proline-containing product step.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_005\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_012\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_008\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Fully integrated hydrothermal-surface-biochemical network route\",\n      \"description\": \"This maximal route connects hydrothermal formate and formaldehyde generation, surface glycolonitrile formation, glyoxylate production, hydrothermal pyruvate synthesis, oxaloacetate convergence, phosphoro-Strecker glycine production, and final literature-limited proline appearance.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_012\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_003\", \"mol_004\", \"mol_006\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_014\", \"mol_012\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_005\", \"mol_006\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_012\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_004\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_002\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_008\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_005\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_007\", \"rxn_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_010\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_007\", \"rxn_011\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": []\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_012\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_005\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "L-Proline", "overall_strategy": "This network is literature-guided and intentionally distinguishes well-supported precursor chemistry from the unresolved final target-forming step. It builds a connected hydrothermal-to-surface-to-biochemical bipartite graph centered on documented prebiotic hubs relevant to proline chemistry: formate, formaldehyde, HCN, glycolonitrile, glyoxylate, pyruvate, oxaloacetate, glycine, and N-phosphoroaminonitrile intermediates. Multiple convergent pathways generate these hubs across alkaline hydrothermal, tidal-flat, evaporitic-pool, and protometabolic settings. The final appearance of L-proline is represented only through the limited literature-supported evidence that proline can arise in reduced hydrothermal mixtures involving formaldehyde addition to glycine, while explicitly acknowledging in reaction reasoning that direct, mechanistically resolved, stereoselective prebiotic synthesis of free L-proline remains unproven.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "CO2", "iupac_name": "carbon dioxide", "common_name": "carbon dioxide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "H2", "iupac_name": "molecular hydrogen", "common_name": "hydrogen", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2/h1H", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "CH2O2", "iupac_name": "methanoic acid", "common_name": "formate/formic acid", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O2/c2-1-3/h1H,(H,2,3)", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "CH2O", "iupac_name": "methanal", "common_name": "formaldehyde", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O/c1-2/h1H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "CHN", "iupac_name": "hydrogen cyan