nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Proline\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network is literature-guided and intentionally distinguishes well-supported precursor chemistry from the unresolved final target-forming step. It builds a connected hydrothermal-to-surface-to-biochemical bipartite graph centered on documented prebiotic hubs relevant to proline chemistry: formate, formaldehyde, HCN, glycolonitrile, glyoxylate, pyruvate, oxaloacetate, glycine, and N-phosphoroaminonitrile intermediates. Multiple convergent pathways generate these hubs across alkaline hydrothermal, tidal-flat, evaporitic-pool, and protometabolic settings. The final appearance of L-proline is represented only through the limited literature-supported evidence that proline can arise in reduced hydrothermal mixtures involving formaldehyde addition to glycine, while explicitly acknowledging in reaction reasoning that direct, mechanistically resolved, stereoselective prebiotic synthesis of free L-proline remains unproven.\n\nMOLECULES (16 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O2 (formate/formic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CHN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H3NO (glycolonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H2O3 (glyoxylic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C4H4O5 (oxaloacetic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_012: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: CH6N2O5P (diamidophosphate) [starting]\n  - mol_014: C2H5N2O3P (glycine N-phosphoroaminonitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C3H4O4 (malonic acid) [starting]\n  - mol_016: C5H9NO2 (L-proline) [target]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_